-- Chilean Stocks: Cencosud, Lan Airlines, Ripley and Salfacorp
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-04-11T20:03:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/chilean-stocks-cencosud-lan-airlines-ripley-and-salfacorp.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa index  fell 0.5 percent to 4,547.14. The  MSCI Chile
index (MXCL)  retreated 0.4 percent to 2,586.4.  Cap SA (CAP)   fell 0.3 percent to 20,202 pesos, its
lowest closing price in about 11 weeks. Chairman Roberto de Andraca said plans by Chile’s largest steel producer and iron-
ore miner to expand its mines in the country may be delayed by
electricity shortages.  Cia. Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU)   rose 1 percent to 7,220
pesos, its second day of gains. Chile’s biggest brewer plans to
use proceeds from a bond sale to expand through acquisitions and
begin operations in a third country, said Chief Executive
Officer Patricio Jottar.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   increased 0.3 percent to 13,942
pesos, ending a six-day losing streak.  Latin America ’s largest
airline by market value reported a 14.7 percent increase in
passenger traffic in March.  Salfacorp SA (SALFACOR)   fell 0.8 percent to 1,120.6
pesos, its lowest closing price since June 2010. Chile’s largest
construction and engineering company has fallen 7.1 percent in
the last two days after it had its  credit rating  reduced by one
level by  Fitch Ratings .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
